@passcombo.com 🏴☠🍋 imo, the key that people seem to be overlooking is that until we bring in those outside people (which miners will not come to OTC without larger incentive than just a fractionally higher profitability to compensated for manual involvement) we need to set a base value (equation if you will) for what we feel what we are doing is going to be worth.
If we say it's of low value, then why should outside investors be interested?
Conversely, if we over-value and "present to the world", then newcomers are going to be put off by that as well.
